**EMBLEM ROGUE**

*A Fire Emblem x Roguelike Tactical RPG*

Game Design Document

Version 1.0 --- February 2026

CONFIDENTIAL

Table of Contents

1\. Game Overview

1.1 Concept

Emblem Rogue is a tactical RPG that blends Fire Emblem's grid-based
combat, class systems, and character progression with roguelike run
structure, randomized encounters, and meta-progression. The game
features SNES-inspired pixel art with modern flourishes, evoking the
aesthetic of classics like Fire Emblem: The Blazing Blade and Octopath
Traveler.

1.2 Core Fantasy

You are a Lord leading a growing warband through a campaign of tactical
battles. Each run, you recruit allies, find equipment, and develop your
force---but defeat means starting over with only your Lord and the
lessons learned. Over many runs, you unlock new classes, improve your
starting capabilities, and discover special characters who join your
permanent roster of potential recruits.

1.3 Platform & Technology

The game is built as a browser-based application using HTML5 Canvas and
JavaScript (Phaser.js framework). All game data (classes, skills, items,
enemies, maps) is defined in JSON for easy iteration and modding.

1.4 Art Style

SNES-era pixel art with a 16x16 or 32x32 base tile size. Character
sprites use a limited, cohesive palette. Battle scenes use side-view
sprite animations. UI is clean and readable with pixel-font text and
modern layout sensibilities.

2\. Core Loop & Run Structure

2.1 The Run

A single run represents one campaign attempt. The player begins with
their Lord (and, through meta-progression, potentially stronger starting
conditions) and progresses through a series of branching nodes leading
to a final boss encounter.

2.2 Campaign Structure

One campaign consists of 3 Acts, each culminating in a boss encounter,
followed by a short Post-Act sequence of elite skirmishes leading to the
Final Boss. A successful run contains roughly 20--25 total battles.

