                                                  warband. Mostly rout
                                                  objectives. Ends with Act 1
                                                  Boss.

  Act 2       6--8        10x8 to     4--5 units  Rising difficulty, more varied
                          12x8                    objectives. Elite enemies
                                                  appear. Ends with Act 2 Boss.

  Act 3       6--8        10x8 to     5--6 units  Full tactical complexity. All
                          12x10                   objectives in play. Ends with
                                                  Act 3 Boss.

  Post-Act    3--4        12x10+      6 units     Elite skirmishes with premium
                                                  rewards leading to the Final
                                                  Boss.
  ----------- ----------- ----------- ----------- -------------------------------

2.3 Node Map (Between Battles)

Between battles, the player navigates a branching node map (similar to
Slay the Spire). Each Act has its own node map with branching paths of
varying risk and reward. Node types include:

-   **Battle:** Standard combat encounter with randomized enemies and
    map. Rewards: XP, gold, choice of 1 loot drop.

-   **Elite Battle:** Tougher encounter against a miniboss drawn from a
    random pool. Rewards: XP, gold, choice of 2 loot drops (higher
    quality).

-   **Boss Battle:** Fixed boss encounter at the end of each Act.
    Non-random, learnable. Rewards: guaranteed powerful item, large XP,
    meta-progression currency.

-   **Recruit Event:** A combat map where a green NPC ally appears. Your
    Lord must reach and speak to them to recruit. The NPC fights
    independently with basic AI but is not suicidal. Recruiting adds
    them to your roster for the run.

-   **Shop:** Spend gold to buy weapons, accessories, skill scrolls, or
    stat boosters. Limited random inventory.

-   **Rest:** Heal all units to full HP. Optionally, a brief narrative
    scene or dialogue.

2.4 Run Failure

When the Lord is defeated in battle, the run ends. The player retains
meta-progression currency earned during the run and returns to the Home
Base to spend it. All recruited units, equipment, and in-run progress
are lost. Special characters return to the recruitment pool for future
runs.

3\. Combat System

3.1 Grid & Turn Structure

Combat takes place on a grid-based map with varied terrain. The game
uses a Player Phase / Enemy Phase turn structure (classic Fire Emblem
style). During Player Phase, all allied units can move and act in any
order. During Enemy Phase, all enemy units act.

3.2 Unit Actions

Each unit can perform one move and one action per turn. Actions include:
Attack (engage an adjacent or ranged enemy), Use Item (consumable from
inventory), Wait (end turn in place), Talk (Lord only, to recruit green
NPCs), Seize (Lord only, on objective tiles), and Trade (swap items with
an adjacent ally).

3.3 Damage Formula

The damage formula follows classic Fire Emblem conventions:

**Physical Damage:** ATK (STR + Weapon Might) − DEF

**Magical Damage:** ATK (MAG + Weapon Might) − RES

**Hit Rate:** Weapon Hit + (SKL × 2) + LCK − Enemy Avoid

**Avoid:** (SPD × 2) + LCK + Terrain Bonus

**Critical Rate:** SKL / 2 + Weapon Crit + Skill Bonuses − Enemy LCK

**Critical Damage:** 3× normal damage

**Double Attack:** If unit's SPD exceeds enemy's SPD by 5 or more, unit
attacks twice.

3.4 Weapon Triangle

The weapon triangle provides a moderate advantage to favorable matchups.
The effect is intentionally lighter than some FE titles to reduce RNG
frustration.

  ----------------- ----------- ----------- -----------------------------
  **Matchup**       **Hit       **Damage    **Notes**
                    Bonus**     Bonus**     

  Swords → Axes     +10 Hit     +1 Damage   Sword users are accurate vs
                                            Axes

  Axes → Lances     +10 Hit     +1 Damage   Axe users overpower Lances

  Lances → Swords   +10 Hit     +1 Damage   Lance users outrange Swords

  Disadvantage      −10 Hit     −1 Damage   Reverse of above
  ----------------- ----------- ----------- -----------------------------

Magic and bows exist outside the weapon triangle. Mastery rank enhances
weapon triangle bonuses to +15 Hit / +2 Damage (and reduces disadvantage
to −5 Hit / −1 Damage).

3.5 Terrain

Terrain tiles affect movement cost, evasion, and defense. Terrain types
are assigned during map generation and add tactical variety.

