  Movement        MOV        Number of tiles a unit can traverse per turn.
  --------------- ---------- ------------------------------------------------

4.2 Experience & Leveling

Units earn XP from combat actions: dealing damage (small XP), defeating
an enemy (large XP), healing allies (moderate XP for staff users), and
completing objectives. XP thresholds increase per level. On level up,
each stat has a chance to increase by 1 based on the unit's growth
rates. Growth rates are expressed as percentages (e.g., 60% STR growth
means a 60% chance STR increases on level up). Level cap is 20 for base
classes and 20 for promoted classes (40 total effective levels).

4.3 Growth Rates

Growth rates come from two sources that stack:

-   **Class Growths:** Each class has a set of growth rates. These are
    semi-randomized within a range when a unit is generated (e.g., a
    Fighter's STR growth might range from 50--70%, rolled once at
    recruitment).

-   **Character Growths:** Lords and Special Characters have fixed
    personal growth rates that add to their class growths. This makes
    them more reliable and distinct. Generic recruited units do not have
    personal growths.

4.4 Promotion

At level 10 or higher, base-class units can promote to an advanced class
using a Promotion Item (found as loot or purchased). Promotion resets
the unit's level to 1 (of the promoted class) while retaining all stats.
Promoted classes gain: stat bonuses on promotion, access to additional
weapon types, a new innate skill (meta-progression required), and higher
stat caps.

