6\. Skill System

6.1 Skill Types

Skills are divided into two categories:

-   **Innate Skills:** Permanently attached to a unit by class or
    character. Cannot be removed or swapped. Unlocked via
    meta-progression: 1 skill for the base class, 1 additional skill on
    promotion.

-   **Equipped Skills:** Found as loot drops (Skill Scrolls) during
    runs. Placed in equip slots. Can be swapped between battles.
    Starting equip slot count: 1. Meta-progression can increase this to
    2--3.

6.2 Skill Categories

Skills fall into broad functional categories:

-   **Combat Skills:** Trigger during attacks (e.g., Astra: 5
    consecutive hits at half damage; Sol: heal for damage dealt; Luna:
    ignore half of enemy DEF).

-   **Passive Skills:** Always active (e.g., Wrath: +20 Crit when below
    50% HP; Vantage: attack first when enemy initiates and HP is below
    50%).

-   **Command Skills:** Activated abilities with cooldowns or per-battle
    limits (e.g., Rally: +4 STR/SPD to adjacent allies for 1 turn).

-   **Personal Skills:** Unique to specific Lords and Special Characters
    (e.g., a Tactician Lord's personal skill might grant +2 to all stats
    for adjacent allies).

6.3 Starting Skills (Meta-Progression)

At the start of a run, units begin with no innate skills by default.
Through meta-progression, the player unlocks innate skills for classes:
one for the base class (available immediately) and one that activates on
promotion. The player can customize which skills their Lord starts with
from a pool of unlocked options. Starting equipped skills for the Lord
are also a meta-progression unlock.

7\. Equipment System

7.1 Equipment Slots

Each unit has two equipment slots: Weapon (required for combat;
determines attack type and range) and Accessory (optional; provides
passive stat bonuses and sometimes special abilities). Units can carry
up to 4 items total in their inventory (weapons, accessories,
consumables) and freely swap between battles.

7.2 Weapons

Weapons are categorized by type (Swords, Lances, Axes, Bows, Tomes,
Light, Staves) and by tier:

