13.2 Save Data

Two types of persistent data: Meta Save (Renown balance, all unlocked
upgrades, unlocked Lords/Special Characters/classes, Lord customization)
and Run Save (current Act/node position, full state of all units
including stats/equipment/skills, inventory, gold, map seed). Meta Save
persists forever via browser localStorage. Run Save is deleted on run
completion or failure.

14\. MVP Scope & Build Order

14.1 MVP Definition

The MVP is a playable vertical slice demonstrating the core loop:
navigate a node map, fight grid-based battles with varied objectives,
recruit units, find loot, level up and promote, fight a boss, and
experience meta-progression. It should include 1 full Act (6--8
battles + 1 boss) and a functional Home Base.

14.2 Build Order

Development should proceed in this order, with each phase producing a
testable result:

1.  **Grid Engine & Movement:** Render a tiled map, place units,
    implement movement ranges and pathfinding. Placeholder art (colored
    squares).

2.  **Combat System:** Implement the damage formula, weapon triangle,
    attack/counterattack, turn phases, and basic enemy AI. This is the
    core --- it must feel right.

3.  **Unit System:** Stats, leveling, growth rates, promotion, weapon
    ranks. Load class data from JSON.

4.  **Equipment & Skills:** Implement equipment effects, skill triggers,
    inventory management.

5.  **Map Generation:** Procedural map generation from templates with
    randomized terrain. Multiple objective types.

6.  **Node Map & Between-Battle Layer:** Branching path selection,
    shops, rest, recruit events.

7.  **Run Loop:** Full run from start to boss: loot drops, recruitment,
    gold economy, run failure.

8.  **Meta-Progression:** Home Base, Renown system, upgrade purchases,
    persistence via localStorage.

9.  **Polish & Art:** Replace placeholders with real sprites, add
    animations, sound effects, music, UI polish.

14.3 Post-MVP Features

Features to add after the MVP is solid: Acts 2 and 3 with escalating
content, additional Lord characters, Special Character roster, full
battle animations, fog of war, additional biomes and tilesets, more
skills and equipment variety, narrative/dialogue system, final boss
multi-phase encounter, and additional meta-progression depth.

